The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Behind the bar

 TANMOY ROY - West View Bar amp; Grill

 For all you teetotallers out there, here?s a sure-fire way to get you into high spirits without a dash of alcohol. Keeping summer in mind and the subtle pastel shades that accompany it, here?s a list of mocktails to suit each person?s colour palette. 

 HAWAIIAN

 Colour: Blue 

 Ingredients: Litchi juice, pineapple juice, blue curacao, vanilla ice cream 

 Method: Put all the ingredients in a blender. Blend nicely. Serve it in a long slim glass (Pilsner) with crushed ice

 STRAWBERRY BLUSH

 Colour: Pink

 Ingredients: Strawberry puree, litchi juice, vanilla ice cream, Sprite

 Method: Blend strawberry puree and litchi juice together.Pour the mix into a Pilsner glass. Top up with Sprite and put a scoop of vanilla ice cream on top to float 

 VERY MERRY RED

 Colour: Crimson 

 Ingredients: Watermelon chunks, lemon chunks, coriander sprigs, sugar, Sprite 

 Method: In an old-fashioned glass, put everything together except Sprite. Muddle it nicely. Pour crushed ice and top up with Sprite. 

 MORNING GLORY

 Colour: Sunshine yellow 

 Ingredients: Apple juice, cinnamon- flavoured tea liquor, lemon juice, Sprite 

 Ingredients: Fill a long glass (Collins) with ice. Pour apple juice and flavoured tea liquor with lemon juice and mix it nicely. Top up with Sprite.

